# Development Workflow

## Core Flow

```
/spec → /test-design + /design (parallel)
  → /contract (fullstack only) → /task
  → /execute (TDD: RED-GREEN-REFACTOR-REVIEW)
  → /exception (backend/fullstack auto)
  → /test (integration/E2E/performance)
  → /archive → /continuous-learning
```

## Entry Point

Use `/workflow "requirement"` as the single entry. It auto-detects mode (frontend/backend/fullstack), dispatches parallel branches, enforces HARD-GATEs, and supports interrupt recovery.

## Principles

- **Spec-First**: All development begins with /spec (BDD format WITH WHEN-THEN)
- **Design-Driven**: /design produces architecture blueprints before any code
- **Test-Complete**: Unit tests in /execute, high-level tests in /test
- **Archive**: /archive merges validated specs into enterprise spec library

## Mode Detection

- `frontend`: UI only, no database, no API contracts
- `backend`: Logic + data, skip frontend steps
- `fullstack`: All steps including api-contract

## HARD-GATE Checkpoints

- Step 5 (execute): test environment must be available before starting
- Step 5.5 (exception): project convention scan must complete
- Step 6 (test): all unit tests from code-execute must pass
